                                                                                            <p style="margin-left:0in;margin-right:0in;"><strong>Chibueze Darlington Anuonye</strong> is the curator of <em>Selfies and Signatures: An Afro Anthology of Short Stories;</em> co-editor of <em>Unbound: An Anthology of New Nigerian Poets Under 40</em> and <em>Daybreak: An Anthology of Nigerian Short Fiction;</em> and editor of <em>Through the Eye of a Needle: Art in the Time of Coronavirus,</em> <em>The Good Teacher</em>, and <em>Who Gave the Order: The History of a People’s Movement</em>. He is a finalist for the 2025 Human Rights Essay Prize.</p>
