</div></div><div class="views-field views-field-field-thumbnail"><div class="field-content imageleft">  <a href="/blog/essay/whipped-angels-wings-french-writer-marc-alyn-pinnacle-his-career-alice-catherine-carls" hreflang="en"><img loading="lazy" src="/sites/worldliteraturetoday.org/files/styles/blog_thumbnail/public/Alyn-anchor_0.jpg?itok=2PKPct2K" width="100" height="75" alt="A collage of Marc Alyn&#039;s book covers" typeof="foaf:Image" class="img-fluid image-style-blog-thumbnail" />

</a>

</div></div><div class="views-field views-field-field-richtitle"><h4 class="field-content"><a href="https://worldliteraturetoday.org/blog/essay/whipped-angels-wings-french-writer-marc-alyn-pinnacle-his-career-alice-catherine-carls">“Whipped by the Angel’s Wings”: French Writer Marc Alyn at the Pinnacle of His Career</a>
</h4></div><div><div class="blog-summary">The year 2025 has been a remarkable one for French writer Marc Alyn (b.&nbsp;1937). First, La Rumeur libre published his three-volume collected works…
</div></div><span class="views-field views-field-field-date"><span class="field-content date-display-single">August 25, 2025
</span></span>|<span><span class="field-name-field-blogauthor"><a href="/author/alice-catherine-carls" hreflang="en">Alice-Catherine Carls</a>
</span></span></div>

